column3:
<UIForeground>F201FC</UIForeground><UIGlow>F201FD</UIGlow> Quest Sync<UIGlow>01</UIGlow><UIForeground>01</UIForeground>
Jonquinet requires a sturdy back to assist him.
Plant the experimental seeds at the designated locations.

Might you have some time to spare for an old researcher, <If(PlayerParameter(4))>lass<Else/>lad</If>? Physical labor doesn't come to me as easily as it once did, and I'm in search of someone a bit more spry to assist me.
The task is a simple one, rest assured. You need only plant these experimental seeds in the nearby fields. You would be compensated for your troubles, of course.
No special skills are required of you. If you've planted one seed, you've planted most of them. Well then, I look forward to seeing what you can do.
You have the seeds, yes? I expect you know what to do with them. If not, well...I'm afraid we may have more troubling issues at hand.
Slightly flushed, are you? Good. I take it that means you've planted the seeds. You have my thanks, and if all goes to plan, the realm's as well.
You see, my research involves the production of nutrient-rich plants that can be harvested in greater numbers than any we have seen thus far.
However, even the most extraordinary crop is useless if they cannot be planted and raised by the common <If(PlayerParameter(4))>woman<Else/>man</If>.
I've long made ease of use a priority when I develop new seeds, asking everyone from experienced researchers to eager children to plant them in the earth and then comparing results.
But of course, I'm sure you've had more than enough long-winded explanations over your journeys to last a lifetime. Take this reward for your contribution, and take satisfaction in a job well done.
